        <span class="current">P2P Transfers</span>
      </nav>

      <!-- Page Title -->
      <h1 class="page-title" id="cp2p_title">Person-to-Person Transfers</h1>
      <p class="page-subtitle">Send, receive, and request money instantly from anyone in the MPay Network. P2P transfers are fast, secure, and fee-free for standard transactions.</p>

      <!-- P2P Illustration -->
      <div class="p2p-illustration" aria-hidden="true">
        <div class="p2p-phone">
          <i class="fa fa-mobile-alt"></i>
          <span>Sender</span>
        </div>
        <div class="p2p-arrow">
          <div class="p2p-arrow-line">
            <div class="dots">
              <span class="dot"></span>
              <span class="dot"></span>
              <span class="dot"></span>
            </div>
            <i class="fa fa-arrow-right"></i>
          </div>
          <div class="p2p-amount">$50.00</div>
        </div>
        <div class="p2p-phone">
          <i class="fa fa-mobile-alt"></i>
          <span>Receiver</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Transfer Methods -->
      <div class="transfer-methods-grid">
        <div class="transfer-method-card">
          <div class="transfer-method-icon">
            <i class="fa fa-paper-plane"></i>
          </div>
          <h4>Send Money</h4>
          <p>Transfer funds to any MPay user instantly</p>
        </div>
        <div class="transfer-method-card">
          <div class="transfer-method-icon">
            <i class="fa fa-inbox"></i>
          </div>
          <h4>Receive Money</h4>
          <p>Accept transfers via QR code or username</p>
        </div>
        <div class="transfer-method-card">
          <div class="transfer-method-icon">
            <i class="fa fa-hand-holding-usd"></i>
          </div>
          <h4>Request Payment</h4>
          <p>Send payment requests to other users</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Section: Sending Money -->
      <section class="doc-section" id="cp2p_content_send">
        <h2 id="sending-money">Sending Money</h2>

        <div class="section-intro">
          <div class="section-intro-icon">
            <i class="fa fa-paper-plane"></i>
          </div>
          <div class="section-intro-content">
            <h4>Quick & Secure Transfers</h4>
            <p>Send money to anyone on the MPay Network in seconds. You can send via username, phone number, or QR code — whichever is most convenient.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h3 id="send-by-username">Send by Username or Phone Number</h3>
        <p>The most common way to send money is by searching for the recipient using their MPay username or registered phone number.</p>

        <div class="steps">
          <div class="step">
            <div class="step-number">1</div>
            <div class="step-title">Open the P2P Transfer Screen</div>
            <div class="step-content">From the home screen, tap the <strong>Send</strong> button. You can also navigate to <strong>Transfers → Send Money</strong> from the main menu.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="step">
            <div class="step-number">2</div>
            <div class="step-title">Find the Recipient</div>
            <div class="step-content">Enter the recipient's MPay username or phone number in the search field. The app will show matching users in real-time. You can also select from your <strong>Recent Contacts</strong> or <strong>Favorites</strong> list.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="step">
            <div class="step-number">3</div>
            <div class="step-title">Enter the Amount</div>
            <div class="step-content">Type the amount you want to send. The app will display your current balance and any applicable limits. You can optionally add a note or memo (e.g., <code>Dinner split</code>).</div>
          </div>
          <div class="step">
            <div class="step-number">4</div>
            <div class="step-title">Review and Confirm</div>
            <div class="step-content">Review the transfer details including recipient, amount, and any fees. Tap <strong>Confirm & Send</strong> and authenticate with your PIN or biometric.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="step">
            <div class="step-number">5</div>
            <div class="step-title">Transfer Complete</div>
            <div class="step-content">You'll see a confirmation screen with a transaction reference number. The recipient is notified instantly.</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h3 id="send-by-qr">Send via QR Code</h3>
        <p>If the recipient is nearby, you can scan their personal QR code to send money without needing to search for their account.</p>

        <div class="steps">
          <div class="step">
            <div class="step-number">1</div>
            <div class="step-title">Tap "Scan to Send"</div>
            <div class="step-content">From the Send screen, tap the <strong>QR code icon</strong> in the top right to activate your camera scanner.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="step">
            <div class="step-number">2</div>
            <div class="step-title">Scan the Recipient's QR Code</div>
            <div class="step-content">Point your camera at the recipient's personal MPay QR code. Their profile will be loaded automatically.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="step">
            <div class="step-number">3</div>
            <div class="step-title">Enter Amount and Confirm</div>
            <div class="step-content">Enter the transfer amount, review the details, and confirm with your PIN or biometric authentication.</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="callout info">
          <div class="callout-icon"><i class="fa fa-info-circle"></i></div>
          <div class="callout-content">
            <strong>Tip</strong>
            <p>Save frequently used recipients as <strong>Favorites</strong> for quick access. Long-press on any contact in the Recent list to add them to Favorites.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h3 id="transfer-limits">Transfer Limits</h3>
        <p>Transfer limits depend on your account verification level:</p>

        <div class="limits-table-wrapper">
          <table class="limits-table">
            <thead>
              <tr>
                <th>Verification Level</th>
                <th>Per Transaction</th>
                <th>Daily Limit</th>
                <th>Monthly Limit</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td><span class="badge badge-blue">Basic</span></td>
                <td>$250</td>
                <td>$500</td>
                <td>$2,000</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><span class="badge badge-green">Verified</span></td>
                <td>$2,500</td>
                <td>$5,000</td>
                <td>$25,000</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><span class="badge badge-purple">Premium</span></td>
                <td>$10,000</td>
                <td>$25,000</td>
                <td>$100,000</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <div class="callout warning">
          <div class="callout-icon"><i class="fa fa-exclamation-triangle"></i></div>
          <div class="callout-content">
            <strong>Important</strong>
            <p>To increase your limits, complete the full KYC verification process. Go to <strong>Settings → Account → Verification</strong> to upgrade.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Section: Receiving Money -->
      <section class="doc-section" id="cp2p_content_receive">
        <h2 id="receiving-money">Receiving Money</h2>

        <div class="section-intro">
          <div class="section-intro-icon">
            <i class="fa fa-inbox"></i>
          </div>
          <div class="section-intro-content">
            <h4>Instant Incoming Transfers</h4>
            <p>When someone sends you money, it arrives in your wallet instantly. You'll receive a push notification and the amount is immediately available to spend.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h3 id="receive-notification">Transfer Notifications</h3>
        <p>When a P2P transfer is sent to your account, you'll receive:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Push notification</strong> — Shows sender name, amount, and memo</li>
          <li><strong>In-app notification</strong> — Available in the Notifications center</li>
          <li><strong>Email notification</strong> — If enabled in your notification settings</li>
          <li><strong>SMS alert</strong> — For amounts above your configured threshold</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 id="share-qr">Share Your QR Code</h3>
        <p>Make it easy for others to send you money by sharing your personal QR code:</p>

        <div class="steps">
          <div class="step">
            <div class="step-number">1</div>
            <div class="step-title">Open Your QR Code</div>
            <div class="step-content">From the home screen, tap <strong>Receive</strong> or go to <strong>Profile → My QR Code</strong>.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="step">
            <div class="step-number">2</div>
            <div class="step-title">Set an Amount (Optional)</div>
            <div class="step-content">You can pre-fill an amount by tapping <strong>Set Amount</strong>. This generates a QR code that includes the payment amount, so the sender doesn't need to enter it manually.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="step">
            <div class="step-number">3</div>
            <div class="step-title">Share or Display</div>
            <div class="step-content">Show the QR code on your screen for the sender to scan, or tap <strong>Share</strong> to send it via message, email, or social media.</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="screenshot-placeholder">
          <i class="fa fa-image"></i>
          <span>Personal QR Code screen with amount field</span>
        </div>

        <h3 id="share-username">Share Your Username or Payment Link</h3>
        <p>You can also share your payment details in other ways:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Username</strong> — Share your @username for others to find you in the app</li>
          <li><strong>Payment Link</strong> — Generate a unique link that opens the MPay app with your details pre-filled</li>
          <li><strong>Phone Number</strong> — If linked to your account, others can find you by phone number</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="code-block">
          <div class="code-block-header">
            <span>Payment Link Format</span>
            <button class="copy-btn">Copy</button>
          </div>
          <pre>https://pay.mpaynetwork.com/u/<span class="property">@yourusername</span>
https://pay.mpaynetwork.com/u/<span class="property">@yourusername</span>?<span class="keyword">amount</span>=<span class="string">50.00</span>&<span class="keyword">note</span>=<span class="string">dinner</span></pre>
        </div>

        <div class="callout success">
          <div class="callout-icon"><i class="fa fa-check-circle"></i></div>
          <div class="callout-content">
            <strong>No Fees for Receiving</strong>
            <p>Receiving P2P transfers on MPay Network is always free. There are no fees for incoming standard transfers.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Section: Requesting Money -->
      <section class="doc-section" id="cp2p_content_request">
        <h2 id="requesting-money">Requesting Money</h2>

        <div class="section-intro">
          <div class="section-intro-icon">
            <i class="fa fa-hand-holding-usd"></i>
          </div>
          <div class="section-intro-content">
            <h4>Payment Requests Made Easy</h4>
            <p>Need to collect money from a friend or split a bill? Send a payment request directly from the app. The recipient gets a notification and can pay with a single tap.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h3 id="send-request">Sending a Payment Request</h3>

        <div class="steps">
          <div class="step">
            <div class="step-number">1</div>
            <div class="step-title">Open Request Screen</div>
            <div class="step-content">From the home screen, tap <strong>Request</strong>. You can also navigate to <strong>Transfers → Request Money</strong>.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="step">
            <div class="step-number">2</div>
            <div class="step-title">Select Recipient(s)</div>
            <div class="step-content">Search for one or multiple users. For bill splitting, you can select multiple contacts and the app will divide the amount equally or let you set custom amounts for each person.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="step">
            <div class="step-number">3</div>
            <div class="step-title">Set the Amount and Details</div>
            <div class="step-content">Enter the total amount and add a description (e.g., <code>Dinner at La Piazza - March 15</code>). For split requests, choose between <strong>Equal Split</strong> or <strong>Custom Amounts</strong>.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="step">
            <div class="step-number">4</div>
            <div class="step-title">Send the Request</div>
            <div class="step-content">Review the request details and tap <strong>Send Request</strong>. Each recipient will receive a push notification with the payment request.</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h3 id="manage-requests">Managing Payment Requests</h3>
        <p>Track all your pending, completed, and expired requests in one place:</p>

        <ul>
          <li><strong>Pending</strong> — Requests awaiting payment from the recipient</li>
          <li><strong>Completed</strong> — Requests that have been paid</li>
          <li><strong>Declined</strong> — Requests that the recipient has declined</li>
          <li><strong>Expired</strong> — Requests that were not responded to within 30 days</li>
        </ul>

        <p>To view your requests, go to <strong>Transfers → My Requests</strong>. You can also:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Send a reminder</strong> — Tap on a pending request and select "Remind"</li>
          <li><strong>Cancel a request</strong> — Swipe left or tap "Cancel" on any pending request</li>
          <li><strong>Resend an expired request</strong> — Open the expired request and tap "Resend"</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 id="respond-to-request">Responding to a Payment Request</h3>
        <p>When someone sends you a payment request, you have several options:</p>

        <div class="steps">
          <div class="step">
            <div class="step-number">1</div>
            <div class="step-title">Review the Request</div>
            <div class="step-content">Tap the notification or go to <strong>Transfers → Incoming Requests</strong>. Review the requester, amount, and description.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="step">
            <div class="step-number">2</div>
            <div class="step-title">Pay or Decline</div>
            <div class="step-content">Tap <strong>Pay Now</strong> to fulfill the request instantly, or tap <strong>Decline</strong> if you don't want to pay. You can optionally add a note when declining.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="step">
            <div class="step-number">3</div>
            <div class="step-title">Authenticate</div>
            <div class="step-content">If paying, confirm with your PIN or biometric authentication. The money is transferred immediately.</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="callout info">
          <div class="callout-icon"><i class="fa fa-info-circle"></i></div>
          <div class="callout-content">
            <strong>Bill Splitting Pro Tip</strong>
            <p>When splitting a bill, you can attach a photo of the receipt to the request. This helps recipients verify the amount and increases payment speed.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="callout danger">
          <div class="callout-icon"><i class="fa fa-shield-alt"></i></div>
          <div class="callout-content">
            <strong>Fraud Warning</strong>
            <p>Never pay a request from someone you don't know. If you receive an unexpected payment request, verify the sender before paying. Report suspicious requests via <strong>Settings → Report an Issue</strong>.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- FAQ Section -->
      <section class="doc-section faq-section" id="cp2p_faq_accordion">
        <h2 id="faq">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq1-answer" tabindex="0">
            <span>Are P2P transfers free?</span>
            <i class="fa fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer" id="faq1-answer" role="region">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              <p>Yes, standard P2P transfers between MPay wallet users are completely free. There are no fees for sending or receiving money. However, instant transfers to external bank accounts may incur a small fee (typically 1-2%).</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq2-answer" tabindex="0">
            <span>How long does a P2P transfer take?</span>
            <i class="fa fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer" id="faq2-answer" role="region">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              <p>P2P transfers between MPay users are instant — the money appears in the recipient's wallet within seconds. In rare cases during high traffic, transfers may take up to 30 seconds to process.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq3-answer" tabindex="0">
            <span>Can I cancel a P2P transfer after sending?</span>
            <i class="fa fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer" id="faq3-answer" role="region">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              <p>Once a P2P transfer is confirmed and sent, it cannot be reversed. If you sent money to the wrong person, you can contact the recipient through the app to request they send it back. You can also open a dispute through <strong>Help → Report a Problem</strong> within 24 hours.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq4-answer" tabindex="0">
            <span>Can I send money to someone who doesn't have MPay?</span>
            <i class="fa fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer" id="faq4-answer" role="region">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              <p>You can invite non-MPay users to receive transfers. When you send money to a phone number not registered on MPay, the recipient receives an SMS with a link to download the app and claim the funds. Unclaimed transfers expire after 14 days and are automatically refunded.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq5-answer" tabindex="0">
            <span>How do I increase my transfer limits?</span>
            <i class="fa fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer" id="faq5-answer" role="region">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              <p>Transfer limits are tied to your account verification level. To increase your limits:</p>
              <p>1. Go to <strong>Settings → Account → Verification</strong>.<br>2. Complete the required verification steps for the next level.<br>3. Limits are updated automatically once verification is approved (typically within 24 hours).</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq6-answer" tabindex="0">
            <span>What happens if I send money to the wrong person?</span>
            <i class="fa fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer" id="faq6-answer" role="region">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              <p>If you accidentally send money to the wrong recipient, you should:</p>
              <p>1. Contact the recipient through the app's in-built messaging feature to request a return.<br>2. If the recipient is unresponsive, file a dispute within 24 hours through <strong>Help → Report a Problem → Wrong Recipient</strong>.<br>3. Our support team will mediate the situation. Please note that we cannot guarantee recovery of funds sent to the wrong person.</p>
              <p>Always double-check the recipient's name and profile picture before confirming a transfer.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq7-answer" tabindex="0">
            <span>Can I schedule recurring P2P transfers?</span>
            <i class="fa fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer" id="faq7-answer" role="region">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              <p>Yes! You can set up recurring transfers for rent payments, allowances, or regular payments. After entering the transfer details, toggle on <strong>Make Recurring</strong> and choose your frequency (weekly, bi-weekly, or monthly). You can manage or cancel recurring transfers in <strong>Transfers → Scheduled</strong>.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Prev/Next Navigation -->
      <nav class="prev-next-nav" id="cp2p_prev_next" aria-label="Page navigation">
